div.div: - Studio keeps "dynamic" configuration in their database. It is importent to keep as much configuration as possible there to decouple it from source code.
- E.g. saving Maskinporten scopes for an app only stores the config to DB (everything is still just design-time)
- Building an app only touches Gitea - which is the source code and "static" config
- Releasing an app combines build output (container image) and dynamic config

TRADEOFFS
+ 1 transactional boundary for initial writes (good for UX)
+ Great built-in capabilties for reliable eventual consistency in Kubebuilder/controller-runtime

+ There is a dedicated place for "dynamic" config, covering scenarios above
~ Coupling towards infra (k8s)
- Config is exposed to app (incl. secrets managed by us)
- Supplier credentials are distributed widely (though maintained in a single place)
- Some domain knowledge will be kept in a very different tech landscape

* Golang, k8s/controller-runtime
* For team Apps: how runtime dependencies are managed, lifecycle etc
~ Team Apps build it, team Platform run it?
